 White normativity is an ideological commitment and a form of racialized discourse that comes from the social actions of those involved in the ELT profession; this normative model or ideal standard constructs a system of racial discrimination that is founded on White privilege, saviorism and neoliberalism. Drawing on a wide range of data sources, this book is a must-read for anyone interested in critically examining ELT.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingxKorean speakers. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzKorea (South). 0aEnglish language--Study and teaching--Korea (South). 0aRacism in education. 0aSecond language acquisitionxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh  aELT .  aKorea.  aRace.  aWhiteness.  acritical ELT.  adiscrimination.  alanguage teaching.  aracism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066312908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309843940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783098439423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783098439/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066312-9  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE